AMA Code of Medical Ethics 1997 edition by the Council on Ethical and
Judicial Affairs.

Page 17 sction 2.08
Commercial Use of Human Tissue
(3)Human tissue and its products may not be used for commercial purposes
without he informed consent of the patient who provided the original cellular
material.  

based on the report "Who Should Profit from the Economic Value of Human
Tissue? An Ethical Analsysis. issued June 1990.
